{{Quote|My initial recommendation: Cancel the invasion of Zeltros and try a world that's less populated. Perhaps even unpopulated.|[[Ensign/Legends|Ensign]] [[Phoebe]]|<ref name="Zeltros: Pleasure Planet">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/sw20040105zeltros|text=Zeltros: Pleasure Planet|int=Zeltros: Pleasure Planet}}</ref>}}
'''Operation: Glorious Destiny''' was the failed plot of the [[Hiromi Empire]] to conquer part of the [[Galaxy/Legends|galaxy]] through inciting war among the members of the [[Alliance of Free Planets]]. Overall, it failed miserably, though they did come close to inciting war between member worlds [[Endor/Legends|Endor]] and [[Lahsbane/Legends|Lahsbane]] and assassinating the Alliance's leaders by means of a bomb. Only a series of freak coincidences foiled [[Executive officer/Legends|First Officer]] [[Hirog]]'s attempts.

Their [[Battle of Zeltros|invasion]] of [[Zeltros/Legends|Zeltros]] was likewise foiled by an unforeseen coincidence; two other simultaneous invasions, by the [[Nagai/Legends|Nagai]] and the [[Tof/Legends|Tofs]]. Ultimately though, Operation: Glorious Destiny produced peace for the Hiromi Empire, after they signed a peace treaty with the Alliance and gained full membership.

